# Pre-Researcher — Sanctuary Worship Playback Engine

## Priority 1: Stem Audio Source

**Verdict: Activate programmatic fallback. No suitable no-login, permissive CC stems found.**

Investigated sources:
- **Tommy Walker Ministries** (tommywalkerministries.org/multitracksmenu): Free tracks but require cart checkout (account/email). One direct Dropbox URL found for "He Is The Lord (Isaiah 40)" but it contains only click+cues WAV/MP3, not full stem set (drums/bass/keys/pads). Not usable as-is.
- **WorshipBackingBand**: HTTP 403 — requires login.
- **Cambridge-MT**: Massive mixing library (fully CC for practice use) but search page returned 403; genre skews pop/rock, no confirmed worship/CCM stem packs with separated drums+bass+keys+pads.
- **Freesound.org**: No complete multitrack worship packs confirmed — individual samples only.
- **MxU / LoopCommunity / PraiseCharts**: All require account signup before download.

**Recommendation:** Use the programmatic OfflineAudioContext fallback as specified in plan.md. This eliminates all licensing risk and is fully self-contained. Song 2 can share the same generated stems with different BPM/section/cue metadata. Do NOT block build on external stems.

If a real audio file is desired: the Tommy Walker "He Is The Lord (Isaiah 40)" click+cues Dropbox (`https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/0h4l7cvbmyjig05laclqu/h?dl=0&rlkey=ph2mb5zugakzzsxyvdp7ygopn`) can provide a realistic click reference, but other stems must be programmatic.

