## Priority 2: Visual Design Refs

### MultiTracks Playback (iOS/Mac app)
- **Mixer**: Per-track volume slider, mute, solo. "Auto Fade" auto-reduces non-click/guide tracks. "Auto Pan" separates click/guide to separate output channels.
- **Sections**: Named section chips in song order; "Live ReOrder" lets you drag sections during performance (double-tap). "Dynamic Guide Cues" auto-update when arrangement changes.
- **Transport**: Live Crossfade between songs/pads; transition modes (AutoLink, Overlap, Crossfade); configurable start/end points with optional 5s fade.
- **Loop**: Live Loop + Infinite Loop with MIDI controller assignment; MIDI mapping to jump to any section.
- **Key UX pattern**: Section chips are primary navigation; mixer is horizontal strips below timeline; transport pinned top.

### Loop Community Prime (iOS/Mac app)
- **Mixer**: Unlimited tracks, per-track volume/mute/solo. Audio interface routing (each stem to a separate physical output).
- **Sections**: Section markers built-in; section looping (loop any section). All purchased split tracks auto-include section markers.
- **Click/Cue**: Multiple click metronome sounds; cue voices in English, Spanish, Portuguese.
- **Arrangement**: Drag-and-drop section reorder; setlist management with saved song arrangements.
- **Key UX pattern**: Dark professional aesthetic; section chips across top of song view; mixer strips below.

**Design synthesis for Sanctuary:** Both apps use dark console aesthetic (confirms plan tokens), horizontal channel strips at bottom, section chips as primary navigation above waveform, transport pinned top. Plan layout is correct.

